name: aiken-county-technology-laboratory-actl
notes: The Aiken County Technology Laboratory (ACTL) was established at Aiken County&#39;s Savannah River Research Campus to provide modern laboratory facilities for SRNL&#39;s unclassified research and development in the fields of waste management, environmental sciences, and biotechnology. The County-owned Research Campus, located adjacent to the Savannah River National Laboratory&#39;s main campus, provides a setting that facilitates collaboration with universities and other institutions. ACTL occupies over 20,000 square feet of laboratory space, including state-of-the-art vitrification furnaces used to support operation of the Savannah River Site&#39;s Defense Waste Processing Facility, bioanalytical support facilities, anaerobic facilities, and 2,000 square feet of high bay space that allows for pilot-scale facilities. The Laboratory also includes conference room amenities.

extras.value: Researchers from SRNL&#39;s Environmental &amp; Chemical Process Technology and Environmental Science &amp; Biotechnology directorates work at ACTL, conducting research and development in the areas of:  Waste Management   Next Generation Waste Pretreatment Advanced Filtration Methods Stabilization Technologies Glass Technology  Environmental Sciences   Novel environmental remediation technologies Petroleum Hydrocarbon Bioremediation Microbial Immobilization of Metals/Radionuclides  Biotechnology   Biohazard Assessment and Mitigation Biocollection Environmental Bioforensics Bioenergy
